INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4000','letter','1776-03-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Alexander','McDougall','','individual','','I am by no means without my apprehensions of danger from that licentiousness which in your situation is not uncommon ; nothing will contribute more to its suppression than a vigorous exertion of the powers vested in your Convention and Committee of Safety','ltr_joj4000.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4001','letter','1776-04-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Alexander','McDougall','','individual','','Many of the reasons you allege for delaying taxation are weighty, and I confess did not occur to me. It is certainly unreasonable to impose on the city, in its present circumstances, so great a share of the public expenses.','ltr_joj4001.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4002','letter','1776-05-29','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','Our Convention will, I believe, institute a better government than the present, which in my opinion will no longer work anything but mischief','ltr_joj4002.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4003','letter','1776-10-11','Fishkill','NY','US','John','Jay','','Edward','Rutledge','','individual','','Let no considerations induce you to excuse General Mifflin from the office of quarter-master-general. Moyland acted wisely and honestly in resigning.','ltr_joj4003.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4004','letter','1777-03-22','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Livingston','','individual','','Your militia bill should have been so framed as to give birth to strong and decisive executive powers.','ltr_joj4004.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4005','letter','1777-03-25','Kingston','NY','US','John','Jay','','Sarah','Livingston','','individual','','We have lately received an uncertain, though unpleasant, account of the enemy\'s landing at Peekskill. How did your nerves bear the shock ? My father and mother, I apprehend, were very uneasy.','ltr_joj4005.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4006','letter','1777-06-05','Kingston','NY','US','John','Jay','','Leonard','Gansevoort','','individual','','Mr. Cuyler informs me, that some of my friends in your county have done me the honour of naming me, among other candidates, for the office of governor.','ltr_joj4006.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4007','letter','1777-07-06','Kingston','NY','US','John','Jay','','Sarah','Livingston','','individual','','When I consider that one of the reasons assigned for the creation of woman was, \"that it is not good for man to be alone,\" I find my present situation condemned, not only by my own feelings, but by divine authority.','ltr_joj4007.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4008','letter','1777-12-11','Fishkill','NY','US','John','Jay','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','As to your loss of influence among a certain body, it is less so than you may imagine. The virtuous and sensible still retain their former sentiments.','ltr_joj4008.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4009','letter','1778-02-12','','','US','John','Jay','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','I hope you will seriously determine to serve your country, at least in a legislative capacity.','ltr_joj4009.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4010','letter','1778-02-26','','NY','US','John','Jay','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','as I have too long kept you in suspense relative to the farm you was so kind as to offer me, I ought now to acquaint you that I am under a necessity of denying myself the pleasure of being your neighbour.','ltr_joj4010.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4011','letter','1778-03-11','','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','Pennsylvania, I believe, is sick unto death. It will nevertheless recover, though perhaps not soon. Weak and bad constitutions incline to chronical disorders.','ltr_joj4011.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4012','letter','1778-04-29','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','I am now engaged in the most disagreeable part of my duty, trying criminals. They multiply exceedingly. Robberies become frequent : the woods afford them shelter, and the tories food.','ltr_joj4012.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4013','letter','1779-01-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','Now is the season for exertion. Attend regularly. Confirm those who esteem you and their country. Convert or confound those who would sacrifice either to private views.','ltr_joj4013.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4014','letter','1779-02-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','The complexions of resignation, of soft complaint, and joyless sensibility, are so blended in your letter, that if anonymous, one would suppose it written by a wayworn traveller through this vale of tears','ltr_joj4014.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4015','letter','1779-02-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','When characters rendered amiable by virtues and important by talents, are exposed to suspicions, and become subjects of investigation, the sensibility of individuals as well as the interest of the public are concerned in the event of the inquiry.','ltr_joj4015.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4016','letter','1779-11-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Kate','Livingston','','individual','','A report has just reached here that the enemy have visited Elizabethtown, and burnt your father\'s house.','ltr_joj4016.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4017','letter','1779-03-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','The state of your politics is much as I expected. I fear some of your measures are more severe than wisdom or humanity will justify.','ltr_joj4017.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4018','letter','1779-03-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','So uncertain has been the fate of letters during the course of this war, that I very seldom write one without adverting to the possibility and consequences of its miscarriage and publication.','ltr_joj4018.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4019','letter','1779-04-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Lincoln','','individual','','Although I have not the honour of a personal acquaintance with you, yet I am so well informed of your character as to believe you will always be happy in leading a young soldier to glory','ltr_joj4019.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4023','letter','1779-10-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Samuel','Huntingdon','','individual','','my conduct in the chair and in the execution of public business has been honoured by the approbation of Congress. The testimony given of it by this act, demands my warmest acknowledgments.','ltr_joj4023.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4024','letter','1779-10-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','The only satisfaction I promise myself from this appointment, will flow from the rectitude with which the duties of it will be discharged, and not from a prospect of general approbation.','ltr_joj4024.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4025','letter','1780-06-00','Aranjuez','','ESP','John','Jay','','Egbert','Benson','','individual','','Our plans of life have, within these few years past, been strangely changed. Our country, I hope, will be the better for the alterations. How far we, individually, may be benefited, is more questionable.','ltr_joj4025.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4026','letter','1780-10-27','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','James','Lovell','','individual','','It is true that I might write to Congress very often, indeed by every vessel, and there are many of them ; but how are my letters to get to the seaside ? By the post ? They would be all inspected, and many suppressed.','ltr_joj4026.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4027','letter','1780-09-17','St Ildefonso','','ESP','John','Jay','','T','MatLack','','individual','','Knowledge is essential to the duration of liberty, and Pennsylvania is wise in making them both the objects of public care.','ltr_joj4027.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4028','letter','1780-10-30','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','Bills to the amount of 100,000 dollars have arrived. A loan cannot be effected here. What the court will do is as yet uncertain, and will long continue so.','ltr_joj4028.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4029','letter','1780-11-19','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','I have lately received a letter from Francis Child, a lad whom I had taken by the hand after his father\'s death, and put apprentice to Mr. Dunlap, your printer.','ltr_joj4029.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4030','letter','1780-11-00','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Egbert','Benson','','individual','','I have a favour to ask of you ; it is that you would make a visit to my father, and send me a minute account of his health, and that of the family. Make a half dozen copies of your letter, and send them','ltr_joj4030.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4031','letter','1781-01-09','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','E','Gerry','','individual','','Your Constitution gives me much satisfaction. It appears to me to be, upon the whole, wisely formed and well digested. I find that it describes your State as being in New-England, as well as in America. Perhaps it would be better if these distinctions were permitted to die away.','ltr_joj4031.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4032','letter','1781-02-21','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','Affairs here begin to wear a better aspect. I am promised 3,000,000 rials, that is, 150,000 dollars, which, though inadequate to the demands upon me, is still a great consolation, especially as men who are at the pains of planting and watering trees, seldom let them perish','ltr_joj4032.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4033','letter','1781-03-00','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Egbert','Benson','','individual','','The vulgar proverb, out of sight, out of mind, always appeared to me in the light of a vulgar error, when applied to old friends and companions. I hope I have not been mistaken','ltr_joj4033.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4034','letter','1781-03-29','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','I take the liberty of sending you a cask of Packaretti, the favourite wine of our late friend, Don Juan, whose death I much lament.','ltr_joj4034.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4035','letter','1781-04-00','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','Notwithstanding my repeated and earnest applications to the Count de Florida Blanca, I have as yet been able to obtain only $34,880 of the 8150,000 expressly promised me in December last.','ltr_joj4035.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4036','letter','1781-04-23','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Charles','Thompson','','individual','','The able manner in which it treats the important subject of American finances induced me to give that part of it to the minister, and to send a copy of the same extract to Dr. Franklin','ltr_joj4036.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4037','letter','1781-06-05','Aranjuez','','ESP','John','Jay','','J','Smith','','individual','','We wait with impatience for further information respecting the military operations in the southern States. Lord Cornwallis\'s expedition bears some marks of rashness, and I cannot but expect he will have some reason to repent it.','ltr_joj4037.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4038','letter','1781-07-09','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','A vessel has arrived at Bilboa, in twenty-four days from Salem. I received by her some family letters, which came from Bilboa under cover to a gentleman here.','ltr_joj4038.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4039','letter','1781-07-14','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Silas','Talbot','','individual','','Not being authorized by Congress to provide for American prisoners in England, I could not justify undertaking it, and therefore referred your application to Dr. Franklin','ltr_joj4039.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4040','letter','1781-07-31','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Frederick','Jay','','individual','','We have heard (though not from you) that a number of armed robbers have paid you a visit, and taken from the family their money, plate, &c. ; it is also said that they behaved towards our father, Peter, and Nancy, with more decency and respect than people of that class generally observe.','ltr_joj4040.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4041','letter','1781-08-01','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Peter','Jay','','individual','','Several letters I have received from Jersey and Philadelphia mention your having been robbed in April last by a number of armed men. It is said, they behaved with uncommon respect to you','ltr_joj4041.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4042','letter','1781-09-08','St Ildefonso','','ESP','John','Jay','','William','Bingham','','individual','','Your representation of the state of our affairs is flattering, and affords reason to hope that the enemy will soon cease to deceive themselves and others by groundless expectations of conquest.','ltr_joj4042.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4043','letter','1781-12-10','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Henry','Knox','','individual','','The harmony subsisting between the French troops and ours, is an agreeable, as well as an important circumstance, and I am glad that the Marquis De La Fayette had an opportunity of cutting some sprigs of laurel on one of the enemy\'s redoubts.','ltr_joj4043.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4044','letter','1782-02-23','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','George','Clinton','','individual','','I congratulate you on the successful issue of the last campaign, to the brilliancy of which the late surrender of Fort St. Philip, at Mahon, has much contributed.','ltr_joj4044.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4045','letter','1782-04-25','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','Mrs. Jay\'s time is much employed in nursing and amusing herself with her little girl. She is writing to Mrs. Morris. We are cheerful, and not unhappy, though distant from our friends','ltr_joj4045.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4046','letter','1782-06-26','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Armand','Marc','','individual','','Your friend, Mons. Risleau, at Bordeaux, pleased me much ; there is a frankness in his manner, and a warmth about his heart, that is very engaging. I made some agreeable acquaintances in that city, and wish I could have staid longer with them.','ltr_joj4046.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4047','letter','1782-08-13','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','Almost ever since my arrival here I have had, and still have, a sick family. The epidemic disorder which has spread through the northern part of Europe has been severe upon us. I am free from it at present, but it has taken from me some flesh and much strength.','ltr_joj4047.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4048','letter','1782-10-13','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','This has led me to make your sons the subject of this letter. It is an interesting one to you, and therefore not indifferent to me.','ltr_joj4048.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4049','letter','1792-10-13','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','I have received your festina Jente letter, but wish it had been at least partly in cipher ; you need not be informed of my reasons for the wish, as by this time you must know that seals are, on this side of the water, rather matters of decoration','ltr_joj4049.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4050','letter','1782-12-04','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Juliana','Penn','','individual','','Your ladyship will, therefore, see the necessity as well as propriety of applying after the war, to the Legislature of Pennsylvania, for a reconsideration of the act respecting your family.','ltr_joj4050.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4051','letter','1782-12-14','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','Some of my colleagues flatter themselves with the probability of obtaining compensation for damages. I have no objections to a further trial, but I confess I doubt its success, for Britain has no money to spare','ltr_joj4051.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4052','letter','1783-01-19','Rouen','','FRA','John','Jay','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','If I am not mistaken, a copy of the American preliminaries has been sent to Spain ; and I flatter myself that Count de Montmorin will think them perfectly consistent with our engagements to our allies.','ltr_joj4052.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4053','letter','1783-02-22','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Silas','Deane','','individual','','The time has been, when my writing to you would not have depended on such a circumstance, for you are not mistaken in supposing that I was once your friend.','ltr_joj4053.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4054','letter','1783-03-28','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Vaughan','','individual','','So far as the peace respects France and America, I am persuaded it was wise in Britain to conclude it. The cessions to France are not, in my opinion, extravagant','ltr_joj4054.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4055','letter','1783-04-08','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','Permit me to introduce to you a gentleman who is going to help you to pay tuxes, and to participate in the liberties which render them necessary, viz. Mr. Joshua Grigley.','ltr_joj4055.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4056','letter','1783-05-11','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Francis','Child','','individual','','You belong to a large and helpless family, and I wish to see you as able, as I hope you would be willing, to provide for them.','ltr_joj4056.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4057','letter','1783-06-13','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have, within these few days past, road and admired your address to the army, and their proceedings in consequence of it.','ltr_joj4057.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4058','letter','1783-07-12','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','M','Livingston','','individual','','I have long been accustomed to hear, and I might add read, so much in which the heart has no concern, that the few letters like yours which reach me, arc particularly welcome.','ltr_joj4058.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4059','letter','1783-07-17','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','Our friend Morris, I suspect, is not a favourite of this court. They say, he treats them as his cashier. They refuse absolutely to supply more money.','ltr_joj4059.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4060','letter','1783-07-19','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','The reluctance with which the States in general pay the necessary taxes, is much to be regretted ; it injures both their reputation and interest abroad, as well as at home, and tends to cherish the hopes and speculations of those who wish we may become and remain an unimportant, divided people.','ltr_joj4060.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4061','letter','1783-07-20','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','Your intended resignation alarmed me, and would have been followed with ill consequences to our affairs. I rejoice that you continue in office, and by no means regret that it will be less in your power than inclination to retire soon.','ltr_joj4061.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4062','letter','1783-09-11','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','I have no reason whatever to believe that you was averse to our obtaining the lull extent of boundary and fishery secured to us by the treaty.','ltr_joj4062.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4063','letter','1783-09-12','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Robert','Livingston','','individual','','Europe hears much, and wishes to hear more of divisions, seditions, violences, and confusions among us. The tories are generally and greatly pitied, more indeed than they deserve.','ltr_joj4063.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4064','letter','1783-09-16','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','While government remains relaxed, and the laws have yet to acquire a due degree of respect and obedience, men of talents, weight, and influence should exert themselves to establish and maintain constitutional authority and subordination.','ltr_joj4064.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4065','letter','1783-09-24','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','I have, as yet, met with neither men nor things on this side of the water which abate my predilection, or, if you please, my prejudices in favour of those on the other.','ltr_joj4065.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4066','letter','1783-09-28','Passy','','FRA','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','The character and talents of delegates to Congress daily become more and more important, and I regret your declining that appointment at this interesting period.','ltr_joj4066.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4067','letter','1783-11-14','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Charles','Thompson','','individual','','In my opinion, no plan or system of conduct respecting America is yet decided upon by the cabinet, in which the jarring principles of whig and tory still strive and ferment.','ltr_joj4067.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4068','letter','1783-12-24','Bath','','ENG','John','Jay','','Kate','Livingston','','individual','','I have letters from Sally almost every week. Thank God, she continues well. She tells me our little girls grow charmingly. My absence from her has been much longer than I expected.','ltr_joj4068.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4069','letter','1784-02-23','Chaillot','','FRA','John','Jay','','Silas','Deane','','individual','','It is painful to say disagreeable things to any person, and especially to those with whom one has lived in habits of friendship ; but candour on this subject forbids reserve.','ltr_joj4069.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4070','letter','1784-02-10','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','You suppose that ill health induces me to resign. You are mistaken. It seldom happens that any measure is prompted by one single motive, though one among others may sometimes have decisive weight and influence.','ltr_joj4070.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4071','letter','1784-02-25','Madrid','','ESP','John','Jay','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','I have never broken the bands of friendship in my life, nor when once broken, have I ever been anxious to mend them.','ltr_joj4071.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4072','letter','1784-03-21','Chaillot','','FRA','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Vaughan','','individual','','The violence of your political storm seems to have abated, but I should not be surprised if you should frequently have March weather.','ltr_joj4072.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4073','letter','1784-04-06','Chaillot','','FRA','John','Jay','','RECIPIENT FIRST','Witherspoon','','individual','','The public, with us, are, in my opinion, so deeply interested in the education of our citizens, that universities, &c, ought no longer to be regarded in the light of mere private corporations. The government should extend to them their constant care','ltr_joj4073.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4074','letter','1784-04-07','Chaillot','','FRA','John','Jay','','Kate','Livingston','','individual','','God only knows what futurity may have in store for us, or what adverse events may still continue to teach us lessons of resignation. It is happy for us, however, that hope is our constant companion','ltr_joj4074.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4075','letter','1784-04-07','Chaillot','','FRA','John','Jay','','Charles','Thompson','','individual','','While I stay, Mr. Norris shall perceive that he could have brought few recommendations to me so acceptable as yours, and those amiable qualities for which you commend him.','ltr_joj4075.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4076','letter','1784-09-02','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Vaughan','','individual','','The health of my family and myself is better than usual, and I begin to flatter myself that if you and Mrs. Vaughan could enjoy this country in only half the degree that I do, you would not greatly regret leaving Old England.','ltr_joj4076.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4077','letter','1784-11-30','Philadelphia','PA','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Vaughan','','individual','','A sufficient number of members to form a Congress not having arrived at Trenton, I passed on to this place ten days ago, to visit my friends.','ltr_joj4077.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4078','letter','1785-01-19','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','Advices from Kentucky inform us that they are threatened with an Indian war ; and there is some room to conjecture that such an event would not be disagreeable to our western neighbours, who, if they do interfere, will certainly be more cunning than wise.','ltr_joj4078.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4079','letter','1785-03-24','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Rush','','individual','','I consider knowledge to be the soul of a republic ; and as the weak and the wicked are generally in alliance, as much care should be taken to diminish the number of the former, as of the latter. Education is the way to do this','ltr_joj4079.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4080','letter','1785-03-31','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','I have the honour of transmitting to you herewith enclosed a certified copy of an act of Congress of the 21st instant, instructing you to communicate to Mr. St. Saphorin','ltr_joj4080.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4081','letter','1785-04-28','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Grand','','individual','','I have accepted the office which Congress was pleased to offer me, and shall be much obliged to vou for such intelligence from time to time as you may think useful for me to receive, and prudent for you to communicate.','ltr_joj4081.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4082','letter','1785-05-31','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Bingham','','individual','','Our frontier posts still have British garrisons, and we are impatient to hear why they are not. evacuated. Mr. Adams, I suppose, is by this time in London ; his letters will remove our suspense on that head.','ltr_joj4082.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4083','letter','1785-07-15','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','Let me request the continuance of your correspondence, and be assured that it will always give me pleasure to communicate to you such intelligence respecting American occurrences as may appear interesting.','ltr_joj4083.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4084','letter','1785-08-13','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Adrienne','Lafayette','','individual','','Our men, for the most part, mind their business, and our women their families ; and if our wives succeed (as most of them do) in \"making home man\'s best delight,\" gallantry seldom draws their husbands from them.','ltr_joj4084.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4085','letter','1785-09-06','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','The frequent solecisms, observable for some years past in the politics of the court of London, render it exceedingly difficult to divine how they will think and act under almost any given circumstances.','ltr_joj4085.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4086','letter','1785-09-27','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Price','','individual','','That men should pray and fight for their own freedom, and yet keep others in slavery, is certainly acting a very inconsistent, as well as unjust and, perhaps, impious part ; but the history of mankind is filled with instances of human improprieties.','ltr_joj4086.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4087','letter','1785-10-04','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Franklin','','individual','','It strikes me that you will find it somewhat difficult to manage the two parties in Pennsylvania. It is much to be wished that union and harmony may be established there, and if you accomplish it much honour and many blessings will result from it.','ltr_joj4087.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4088','letter','1785-10-11','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','Your letters, as yet, are silent respecting the evacuation of our frontier posts. I do not mean to press you either to do or say any thing unseasonably about it ; for there are times and tides in human affairs to be watched and observed.','ltr_joj4088.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4089','letter','1785-11-01','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','We concur so perfectly in sentiment respecting public affairs, and what ought to be done, that I find no occasion to enlarge on those heads.','ltr_joj4089.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4090','letter','1785-11-24','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','','','position','The President Of Congress','Mr. Temple presented to me this morning the commission which I have now the honour of transmitting to your excellency herewith enclosed. It appoints him consulgeneral of his Britannic majesty, throughout the United States of America.','ltr_joj4090.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4091','letter','1786-01-19','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','Congress has been composed of so few States actually represented, as not to have it in their power to pay that attention to their foreign affairs which they would doubtless have otherwise done.','ltr_joj4091.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4092','letter','1786-02-22','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','Nine States are not yet represented in Congress, and therefore the affairs of this department continue in the same state that they were in at the date of my last.','ltr_joj4092.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4093','letter','1786-03-10','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Lushington','','individual','','I have been favoured with your letter of the 22d ult., and immediately communicated it to the committee of our society for promoting the liberation of slaves, and protecting such as may be manumitted.','ltr_joj4093.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4094','letter','1786-04-16','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Lansdown','','individual','','Your lordship\'s conjectures respecting the new principles of trade and finance will probably be realized. We hear of several circumstances which look and promise well.','ltr_joj4094.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4095','letter','1786-04-20','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Lansdown','','individual','','I perfectly agree in sentiment with your lordship, that it much concerns the honour and future intercourse of both countries to have the treaty of peace duly and faithfully executed.','ltr_joj4095.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4096','letter','1786-06-10','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','Successful revolutions and victorious arms have always a degree of splendour about them, which shines at a great distance, and excites admiration, whether well or ill founded.','ltr_joj4096.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4097','letter','1786-07-14','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','Considering the importance of our commerce with Portugal, it gives me pleasure to learn that a treaty with that kingdom was so nearly concluded. Until our affairs shall be more perfectly arranged, we shall treat under disadvantages','ltr_joj4097.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4098','letter','1786-10-27','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','A spirit of licentiousness has infected Massachusetts, which appears more formidable than some at first apprehended. Whether similar symptoms will not soon mark a like disease in several other States is very problematical.','ltr_joj4098.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4099','letter','1786-11-01','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','When government, either from defects in its construction or administration, ceases to assert its rights, or is too feeble to afford security, inspire confidence, and overawe the ambitious and licentious, the best citizens naturally grow uneasy and look to other systems.','ltr_joj4099.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4100','letter','1786-12-12','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Jacob','Reed','','individual','','The recess (if I may so call it) of Congress gives their officers too much leisure at present ; and there is reason to fear, that the members will be as long in convening this year as they were last.','ltr_joj4100.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4101','letter','1787-07-25','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','Permit me to hint whether it would not be wise and seasonable to provide a strong check to the admission of foreigners into the administration of our national government','ltr_joj4101.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4102','letter','1788-09-21','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am not sure that the new government will be found to rest on principles sufficiently stable to produce a uniform adherence to what justice, dignity, and liberal policy may require','ltr_joj4102.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4103','letter','1789-01-03','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Pierce','','individual','','It is as yet exceedingly uncertain who will be senators for this State, and consequently it cannot be even conjectured by what leading motives they will probably be influenced in their appointments.','ltr_joj4103.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4104','letter','1789-07-14','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Charles','Pettit','','individual','','You know it is important that confidence and cordiality subsist between the heads of the departments, that they may, when necessary, unite their efforts to promote their respective operations for the public good.','ltr_joj4104.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4105','letter','1789-11-27','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Fisher','Ames','','individual','','Mr. Sedgwick has given me the same character of Mr. Tucker that you do. There are at present several candidates for the place in question','ltr_joj4105.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4106','letter','1790-02-27','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Dumont','','individual','','As to offices in the gift of other departments, I think it my duty not to interfere, nor to ask favours, it being improper for a judge to put himself under such obligations.','ltr_joj4106.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4107','letter','1790-11-28','Boston','MA','US','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','An individual remarked, that while Congress thought themselves authorized to take such liberties, private property could not be secure in a national bank.','ltr_joj4107.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4108','letter','1791-09-23','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','How far the present fiscal arrangements require amendments or additions, can best be ascertained of the secretary.','ltr_joj4108.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4109','letter','1791-11-02','Hartford','CT','US','John','Jay','','Frederick','Jay','','individual','','A person who says he left New-York last Friday, reports that a putrid disorder prevailed there, and that among many others, it had rendered your house a house of mourning. This unexpected event affects me greatly.','ltr_joj4109.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4110','letter','1793-03-31','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Egbert','Benson','','individual','','I have had the pleasure of seeing Senor Ceracchi, and his model of a monument in honour of the revolution. The design appears to me to be a noble one, worthy the attention of the United States','ltr_joj4110.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4111','letter','1792-09-08','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','No strong declarations should be made, unless there be ability and disposition to follow them with strong measures.','ltr_joj4111.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4112','letter','1792-12-19','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','It is not difficult to perceive that your situation is unpleasant, and it is easy to predict that your enemies will endeavour to render it still more so.','ltr_joj4112.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4113','letter','1794-03-20','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Dugald','Stewart','','individual','','Accept my thanks for the ingenious work which you was so obliging as to send me by Mr. Childs. I have read it with pleasure and improvement: it casts new light on several interesting questions','ltr_joj4113.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4114','letter','1794-04-30','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','Life is uncertain - whether I take your letter with me, or leave it here, it would, in case of my death, be inspected by others, who, however virtuous, might be indiscreet.','ltr_joj4114.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4115','letter','1794-06-23','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','The observations I have hitherto made induce me to believe that the war with France is popular, and that a war with us would be unpopular.','ltr_joj4115.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4116','letter','1794-07-21','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','Among my letters to Mr. Randolph, is one stating an agreement between Lord Grenville and myself for preserving things in a pacific and unaltered state, between us and the British on the side of Canada and the frontiers','ltr_joj4116.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4117','letter','1794-07-23','Pall Mall','','ENG','John','Jay','','John','Anstey','','individual','','I regret my not knowing that you resided at Bath. We passed from Falmouth through that city in our way to this. It would have given me pleasure to have called upon you, and (to use an Indian expression) have brightened the chain.','ltr_joj4117.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4118','letter','1794-08-05','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am this moment returned from a long conference with Lord Grenville. Our prospects become more and more promising as we advance in the business.','ltr_joj4118.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4119','letter','1794-08-12','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','','Hobart','','individual','','The Agricultural Society is incorporated, with a yearly allowance, by government, of three thousand pounds. Their plans are extensive ; they have been singularly industrious, and much has been done.','ltr_joj4119.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4120','letter','1794-08-14','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','','Read','','individual','','We have both heard it asserted that a man\'s character may be discerned from his handwriting ; if that be true, you and our friend, Edward Rutledge, must be as enigmatical and unintelligible as Oliver Cromwell','ltr_joj4120.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4121','letter','1794-07-11','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','I am still unable to say any thing decisive relative to the objects of my mission. Appearances continue to be singularly favourable, but appearances merit only a certain degree of circumspect reliance.','ltr_joj4121.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4122','letter','1794-09-17','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','The secretary\'s letters by Mr. Monroe, and his speech on his introduction to the Convention, have appeared in the English papers. Their impression in this country may easily be conjectured. I wish they had both been more guarded.','ltr_joj4122.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4123','letter','1794-09-11','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','N','Cruger','','individual','','I must go without a fortune for want of knowing how to get one. That, my good friend, is not your case ; having already made one fortune, you certainly know better how to make another than a person who has never made any.','ltr_joj4123.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4124','letter','1794-09-17','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','There is something very pleasant in the reflection, that while war, discord, and oppression triumph in so many parts of Europe, their domination does not extend to our country.','ltr_joj4124.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4125','letter','1794-11-19','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Oliver','Ellsworth','','individual','','The negotiation is terminated by a treaty. It will, with this letter, go by the packet, which, in expectation of this event, has been detained above a week.','ltr_joj4125.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4126','letter','1794-11-19','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am exceedingly anxious to return ; for although I have every other reason to be satisfied with my situation, yet I am not at home. I ought not to conceal from you, that the confidence reposed in your personal character was visible and useful throughout the negotiation.','ltr_joj4126.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4127','letter','1794-11-19','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','My task is done ; whether finis coronat opus, the president, senate, and public will decide.','ltr_joj4127.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4128','letter','1794-11-19','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Rufus','King','','individual','','I send by the packet the fruit of my negotiation - a treaty. I wish that I could go with it, as well that I might again be in my own country, as that I might answer questions on the subject.','ltr_joj4128.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4129','letter','1794-12-18','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','Tench','Coxe','','individual','','Our affairs relative to this country have a promising aspect. The best disposition towards us prevails here, and the indications and proofs of it daily increase.','ltr_joj4129.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4130','letter','1795-01-08','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','David','Hartley','','individual','','It does not appear probable to me that Europe is very speedily to be blessed with a general and lasting peace, or that the period has already arrived when reason and virtue will govern the conduct of the mass of mankind.','ltr_joj4130.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4131','letter','1795-02-25','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','The objects and efforts of the Jacobin societies in America were well known here ; and the fate of our government was considered as being involved in that of the insurrection.','ltr_joj4131.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4132','letter','1795-03-06','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','it is my opinion that the common and popular (not official) language of America, relative to Great Britain, manifested such a disposition as to create serious apprehensions in this country that we should join with the French in the war','ltr_joj4132.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4133','letter','1795-03-18','London','','ENG','John','Jay','','James','Anderson','','individual','','I have been favoured with yours of the 14th instant. It gives me pleasure to observe, that good-will towards America seems to prevail generally in this kingdom','ltr_joj4133.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4134','letter','1795-06-29','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','The enclosed contains my resignation of the office of chief-justice. I cannot quit it without again expressing to you my acknowledgments for the honour you conferred upon me by that appointment','ltr_joj4134.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4135','letter','1796-09-03','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','The article in the treaty, to which you allude, viz. the last, was proposed by me to Lord Grenville, because it seemed probable that when the treaty should for some time have been in operation, defects might become manifest','ltr_joj4135.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4136','letter','1795-12-14','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Washington','','individual','','all my accounts agree in representing the public mind as becoming more and more composed, and that certain virulent publications have caused great and general indignation','ltr_joj4136.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4137','letter','1796-01-19','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Robert','Goodloe','','individual','','I am much obliged to you, sir, for this vindication ; but it being summary and in general terms, and comprehending only one of the points, I think it best, in order to obviate all further questions, to state particularly my sentiments relative to them both.','ltr_joj4137.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4138','letter','1796-02-29','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Lowell','','individual','','Considering the nature of our governments, a succession of demagogues must be expected : and the strenuous efforts of the wise and virtuous will not cease to be necessary to frustrate their artifices and designs.','ltr_joj4138.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4139','letter','1796-02-14','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Uzal','Ogden','','individual','','I am much obliged to you for the books you have been so kind as to send me, and which, with your friendly letter of the 11th inst., were delivered to me yesterday.','ltr_joj4139.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4140','letter','1796-05-01','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Grenville','','individual','','The great questions which have agitated this country since my arrival, may now, I think, be considered as determined. I will therefore no longer postpone thanking your lordship','ltr_joj4140.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4141','letter','1796-05-26','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Br','Thatcher','','individual','','I shall always be happy in opportunities of manifesting to the family of the late Governor Hancock, my respect for his memory.','ltr_joj4141.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4142','letter','1796-05-26','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Vaughan','','individual','','As to political reformations in Europe or elsewhere, I confess that, considering men as being what they are, I do not amuse myself with dreams about an age of reason, prior to the millennium','ltr_joj4142.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4143','letter','1796-06-15','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Hammond','','individual','','I thank you for making to Lord Grenville the intimation I requested relative to the intended present. I shall deem myself sufficiently honoured and gratified, if my endeavours should prove conducive to permanent peace and conciliation between our countries.','ltr_joj4143.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4144','letter','1796-10-20','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Trumbull','','individual','','You are now placed, as you well observe, in a situation delicate and important. Your reflections on it are just and proper.','ltr_joj4144.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4145','letter','1797-02-28','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','It gives me pleasure to learn, that you will endeavour at least to prepare for a history of the American revolution. To obtain competent and exact information on the subject is not the least arduous part of the task','ltr_joj4145.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4146','letter','1797-03-22','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Rush','','individual','','I have received and read with pleasure your elegant eulogium on the late Mr. Rittenhouse. Such attentions to worthy characters, cherish and encourage modest merit.','ltr_joj4146.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4147','letter','1797-06-04','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Grenville','','individual','','It will give you satisfaction to know that the letters I have received from Mr. King and Mr. Gore, make honourable mention of the candour and good faith of your government.','ltr_joj4147.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4148','letter','1797-08-31','New York','NY','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Vaughan','','individual','','I had this afternoon the pleasure of receiving your favour of the 18th inst. Mrs. Jay joins me in sincerely congratulating you and your amiable family on your arrival in this country ; may your expectations of happiness in it be fully realized.','ltr_joj4148.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4149','letter','1797-10-27','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Trumbull','','individual','','The delays of the court of admiralty do not surprise me. I have no faith in any British court of admiralty, though I have the greatest respect for, and the highest confidence in their courts of justice','ltr_joj4149.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4150','letter','1797-11-13','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Timothy','Pickering','','individual','','The recent explosion at Paris has cast most of our calculations and conjectures, relative to the issue of our negotiations with the Directory, very much into the air.','ltr_joj4150.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4151','letter','1798-08-30','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','There are several topics on which I wish to converse with you, and particularly respecting military arrangements at New-York. The rifle corps, and a few of the new light-infantry companies are established.','ltr_joj4151.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4152','letter','1799-01-30','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','But at this period, there certainly are an uncommon number and series of events and circumstances, which assume an aspect unusually portentous. The seeds of trouble are sowing and germinating in our country','ltr_joj4152.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4153','letter','1799-03-29','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Benjamin','Goodhue','','individual','','The expediency of the president\'s declaration, that he would not send another minister to France, until he should receive assurances, &c, was not, in my judgment, unquestionable. There are political considerations against it','ltr_joj4153.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4154','letter','1799-09-03','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Wilberforce','','individual','','Permit me to congratulate you on the promising aspect of affairs in Europe. England stands high, and while just, no one ought to repine at her prosperity.','ltr_joj4154.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4155','letter','1800-02-28','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Samuel','Miller','','individual','','Accept my thanks for the sermon on the death of General Washington, which you was so obliging as to send me. In my opinion, it abounds in excellent sentiments, well arranged and expressed.','ltr_joj4155.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4156','letter','1800-04-24','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','The late revolution in France does not appear to have dissipated the clouds which veiled from our view the fate of that and other countries. As yet, I see little reason to expect the restoration of the Bourbon family','ltr_joj4156.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4157','letter','1800-07-01','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','Theophilus','Parsons','','individual','','The president declared to the Congress that he would never send another legation to Paris, until he received assurances that it would be properly respected.','ltr_joj4157.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4158','letter','1800-12-16','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Sinclair','','individual','','They who feel an interest in the honour of this country, cannot fail of being gratified by every mark of respect to the memory of our late president.','ltr_joj4158.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4159','letter','1801-03-03','Albany','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Lathrop','','individual','','The eighteenth century has been distinguished, as you observe, by great events.','ltr_joj4159.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4160','letter','1804-07-25','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','The philosophic topics of consolation are familiar to you, and we all know from experience how little relief is to be derived from them.','ltr_joj4160.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4161','letter','1804-11-02','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Maria','Jay','','individual','','Our Heavenly Father has called this child home, and the very best wish that you or I could have formed for him. was, that after a long and virtuous abode bore, he might be where he now is.','ltr_joj4161.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4162','letter','1805-10-18','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Murray','','individual','','I have been favoured with your letter of the 2d ultimo, respecting the African Free-school in the city of New-York. It is, in my opinion, a charitable and useful institution, and well entitled to encouragement and support.','ltr_joj4162.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4163','letter','1805-12-29','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Maria','Jay','','individual','','Although I am persuaded that these reflections are not new to you, yet my solicitude about whatever may affect your comfort, prompts me to remind you of them.','ltr_joj4163.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4164','letter','1806-04-11','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Wilberforce','','individual','','It appears to me, that every independent state has, as such, a perfect right at all times, whether at war or at peace, to make grants to and treaties with any other independent state','ltr_joj4164.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4165','letter','1807-04-18','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Beers','','individual','','Every modification of sovereignty has its inconveniences - there is a better and a worse in them all, and no other than a relative perfection in any of them.','ltr_joj4165.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4166','letter','1807-09-13','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','You have the gout, and you extract consolation from it ; this is good moral chymistry. My rheumatism and your gout may perhaps carry us home the farthest way round, but not in an easy chair.','ltr_joj4166.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4167','letter','1809-05-22','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Morris','Miller','','individual','','The information it conveys cannot fail of being grateful to all who prefer the wise and upright policy which distinguished the administration of Washington, to that which of late has distressed and disgraced our country.','ltr_joj4167.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4168','letter','1809-07-24','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','I was called to Albany by the death of the only remaining child of my daughter, whose grief for the loss of her son and of her husband was still fresh and severe.','ltr_joj4168.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4169','letter','1809-11-08','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Wilberforce','','individual','','The patrons of the abolition act, and of the African Institution, certainly do honour, and will probably do more than ordinary good to Great Britain','ltr_joj4169.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4170','letter','1809-08-16','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','A proper history of the United States would have much to recommend it : in some respects it would be singular, or unlike all others','ltr_joj4170.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4171','letter','1810-02-26','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','After lingering through the summer, I found my disorder gradually returning in the autumn. Since the middle of November I have been confined to the house ; but have as yet suffered less this winter than I did the last.','ltr_joj4171.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4172','letter','1810-10-25','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Wilberforce','','individual','','The principles of the English constitution appear to require that the whole number of representatives should be fairly apportioned among the whole number of electors.','ltr_joj4172.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4173','letter','1811-01-00','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','To sow wheat here is like taking a ticket in a lottery ; more blanks than prizes. The fly destroys more than we reap.','ltr_joj4173.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4174','letter','1811-03-29','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','Your letter conveyed to me the first and only information I have received, that a copy of President Washington\'s valedictory address had been found among the papers of General Hamilton, and in his handwriting','ltr_joj4174.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4175','letter','1811-04-23','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Bristed','','individual','','Accept my thanks for the book on the Resources of Great Britain, which you was so obliging as to send me. It abounds in interesting matter','ltr_joj4175.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4176','letter','1811-11-07','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Miller','','individual','','You have certainly had no inconsiderable share of difficulties, dangers, and troubles, and as you justly observe, Providence has carried you through them all, and has also given you consolations and enjoyments.','ltr_joj4176.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4177','letter','1812-03-02','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Peter','Munro','','individual','','When a piece of ground is wanted for a use important to the State, I know that the State has a right to take it from the owner, on paying the full value of it ; but certainly the Legislature has no right to compel a freeholder to part with his land to any of his fellow-citizens','ltr_joj4177.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4178','letter','1812-09-07','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Lee','','individual','','mention is made of a work of your brother, then in the press, viz. \"Memoirs of the War in the Southern Department.\" The subject and the author naturally excited my attention, and my desire to procure a copy.','ltr_joj4178.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4179','letter','1812-12-02','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Calvin','Chapin','','individual','','Such institutions become the religion we profess, and the blessings we enjoy. Be pleased to assure the board that I am very sensible of the honour they have done me','ltr_joj4179.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4180','letter','1813-01-01','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','Whether our religion permits Christians to vote for infidel rulers, is a question which merits more consideration than it seems yet to have generally received, either from the clergy or the laity.','ltr_joj4180.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4181','letter','1813-01-12','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Jeremiah','Evarts','','individual','','Notwithstanding the inducements I have to make frequent visits to New-York, I have not been there for four years past. The state of my health, and the regimen it requires, not permitting me to be far or long from home.','ltr_joj4181.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4182','letter','1813-02-22','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','You request me to be one of the godfathers. Baptism is too generally regarded as being little more than a customary ceremony ; and yet the purpose of it, and the names used on the occasion, show it to be a solemn procedure.','ltr_joj4182.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4183','letter','1813-04-14','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Joseph','McKean','','individual','','Marks of respect to the characters of such men as Dr. Elliot, not only tend to console their afflicted relatives, but also to cherish the virtues by which they were distinguished.','ltr_joj4183.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4184','letter','1813-05-31','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Noah','Webster','','individual','','The literary productions of Britain and America being interesting to each other, many are of opinion, and I concur in it, that the English language and its orthography should be the same in both countries.','ltr_joj4184.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4185','letter','1813-10-25','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','I have chosen for this letter a subject that is more within your province than in mine.','ltr_joj4185.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4186','letter','1814-09-20','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','William','Miller','','individual','','The cold weather you mention has also prevailed here. I do not recollect so cool a summer. Our corn does not look well. The crops of rye were slender ; those of wheat were good.','ltr_joj4186.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4187','letter','1814-11-01','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Timothy','Pickering','','individual','','Every independent nation has, as such, a rightful and exclusive jurisdiction over the country within its acknowledged boundary lines.','ltr_joj4187.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4188','letter','1815-01-09','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','My health continues to wear away, but I seldom suffer severe pain. Conversation, books, and recollections still enable me, with the blessing of Providence, to amuse confinement, and to glide on placidly towards that ocean to which the stream of time is bearing us all.','ltr_joj4188.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4189','letter','1815-03-11','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','Unless discontents should arise between France and Britain, French influence will not soon be very active in America ; and, consequently, will not administer much fuel to renew and feed a flame against England.','ltr_joj4189.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4190','letter','1816-02-14','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Morse','','individual','','As to the work you mention, I am glad you have undertaken it, because it is desirable, and because I expect it will be well performed. It would give me pleasure to afford the aids you request, but the state of my health admits of very little exertion of mind or body.','ltr_joj4190.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4191','letter','1816-05-22','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Mason','','individual','','Accept my thanks for the friendly letter, and for the book which you was so obliging as to send me by my son.','ltr_joj4191.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4192','letter','1816-06-12','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','','Romeyn','','individual','','I rejoice in the institution of that national society, and assure the Board of Managers, that I am very sensible of the honour they have done me, in thus connecting me with it.','ltr_joj4192.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4193','letter','1816-08-08','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Sinclair','','individual','','Your exertions to improve agriculture, and render it more productive, are known and acknowledged.','ltr_joj4193.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4194','letter','1816-10-12','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Murray','','individual','','Whether war of every description is prohibited by the gospel, is one of those questions on which the excitement of any of the passions can produce no light. An answer to it can result only from careful investigation and fair reasoning.','ltr_joj4194.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4195','letter','1816-10-00','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Gouverneur','Morris','','individual','','Having heard much of your discourse before the New-York Historical Society, it gave me pleasure to receieve copy of it, and to find from the direction that I owed it to your friendly attention.','ltr_joj4195.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4196','letter','1818-01-31','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Adams','','individual','','I have not seen Mr. Wirt\'s book, nor heard of the \"passage\" in it, of which your letter contains a copy.','ltr_joj4196.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4197','letter','1818-04-15','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Murray','','individual','','In my letter to you of the 16th October Inst, I hinted that I might perhaps write and send you a few more lines on the question, Whether war of every description is forbidden by the gospel ?','ltr_joj4197.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4198','letter','1819-01-25','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','As you are in the seventy-fifth year of your age, and I in the seventy- fourth of mine, our leases have expired. We are holding over, and others will soon occupy our places.','ltr_joj4198.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4199','letter','1819-02-27','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','John','Murray','','individual','','The lawfulness of the invasion and conquest of Canaan, being made by express Divine command, is indubitable. It does not decide the question, whether any wars, unless so commanded, are permitted by the moral law','ltr_joj4199.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4200','letter','1819-12-21','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Daniel','Raymond','','individual','','The remarks and statements contained in it place the pernicious influence of slavery on the welfare of our country in conspicuous and impressive points of view.','ltr_joj4200.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4201','letter','1820-12-26','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','Men who are ardent in the pursuit of influence and its fruits, and more attentive to the prosecution than to the propriety of their schemes, usually become and remain hostile to those who steadfastly disapprove of their manoeuvres.','ltr_joj4201.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4202','letter','1821-01-13','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','George','Otis','','individual','','I have received your letter of the 23d ult. expressing a desire that Botta\'s History and your Translation of it may have my approbation','ltr_joj4202.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4203','letter','1821-03-12','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Richard','Peters','','individual','','My letter to you of the 20th December last, contained some remarks relative to the perversions and obliquities which you had noticed, and which I observed were neither recent nor unexpected.','ltr_joj4203.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4204','letter','1821-04-24','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Lindley','Murray','','individual','','We have both experienced afflicting dispensations. Your portion of health has for a long time been diminished ; and I have not had a well day for the last twelve years.','ltr_joj4204.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4205','letter','1821-04-30','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','E','Brown','','individual','','Controversies between the national and a state government, or any of their respective departments, are to be regretted. It is desirable that the one which occasioned this report, should be brought to an amicable and satisfactory termination','ltr_joj4205.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4206','letter','1821-12-03','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Noah','Webster','','individual','','Your Dictionary will doubtless derive utility and reputation from the extensive investigations you mention. The assiduity with which you have for many years persevered, and still persevere, in accomplishing that arduous task, will, I hope, be followed by results','ltr_joj4206.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4207','letter','1822-07-28','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Edward','Livingston','','individual','','That the government of a State should have authority to appoint \"particular days for rendering thanks to God\" for any signal blessing, or imploring his assistance \"in any public calamity,\" is certainly proper.','ltr_joj4207.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_joj4208','letter','1827-01-23','Bedford','NY','US','John','Jay','','Peter','Van Schaack','','individual','','A kind Providence has extended our lives to the commencement of another year. Very few of our early a ciates remain with us.','ltr_joj4208.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life John Jay With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers. by His Son, William Jay in Two Volumes. Vol. II., 1833.');
